00:22:55.510 --> 00:22:56.010
- Lunch.

00:23:16.500 --> 00:23:19.670
- We are now skirting the edge
of the North Pacific Gyre,

00:23:19.670 --> 00:23:22.534
roughly 1,000 miles
east of Hawaii.

00:23:22.534 --> 00:23:24.470
And we're finding
lots of plastic

00:23:24.470 --> 00:23:25.950
on the surface of the ocean.

00:23:25.950 --> 00:23:30.290
- It's mostly small fragments--
blue, green, white, and black,

00:23:30.290 --> 00:23:33.090
among many different
kinds of zooplankton.

00:23:33.090 --> 00:23:36.205
Everywhere you go in North
Pacific Ocean, we find plastic.

00:23:44.424 --> 00:23:46.840
- So I filleted this fish,
thinking we're going to eat it.

00:23:46.840 --> 00:23:47.920
And here's what I found.

00:23:52.780 --> 00:23:53.666
It's full of plastic.

00:23:53.666 --> 00:23:55.540
This is the whole reason
that we're out here,

00:23:55.540 --> 00:23:57.550
to bring this to your attention.

00:23:57.550 --> 00:23:58.880
The plastic isn't benign.

00:23:58.880 --> 00:24:00.400
The fish won't pass it.

00:24:00.400 --> 00:24:03.770
The plastic is full of
persistent organic pollutants,

00:24:03.770 --> 00:24:07.330
things like PCB,
DDT, PAHs, things

00:24:07.330 --> 00:24:09.910
that are known human
carcinogens and endocrine

00:24:09.910 --> 00:24:11.930
disruptors, things you
don't want in your body.

00:24:11.930 --> 00:24:14.952
But they're in the
fish that we eat.

00:24:14.952 --> 00:24:16.410
- I don't want
plastic in my sushi.

00:24:28.257 --> 00:24:28.840
